ABUJA – The Executive Governor of Kano State, His Excellency DR. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje, will on Monday 7 March, 2022 unveil the Theme and Logo of Dala Dry Port at Transcorp Hilton Hotel Abuja. According to a statement by Mallam Mohammed Garba, Honourable Commissioner information, Kano State, the unveiling is prelude to Kano Economic Investment summit which will showcase the Dala Dry Port as a major transport infrastructure and other sector like the Kano economic city that will stimulate industrialisation and commerce. The Dry port will make Kano a hub of domestic and international trade, thereby diversify the economic base of the country. National Convention: APC Inaugurates 20 Sub-Committees March 7 Groups Urge INEC To Review Ogoja/Yala Federal Constituency… The unveiling of the Logo and Theme shall have in attendance major stakeholders in the industry including; the Nigerian Shippers’ Council (NSC), the Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA), the Nigerian Customs Service (NCS), the Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency, (NIMASA), the Shipping lines, the Infrastructure Concession Regulatory Commission (ICRC), the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), the Nigerian Railway Corporation (NRC), National Inland water ways Authority (NIWA) and Council for Regulation of Freight Forwarding (CRFFN). The Chairman Dangote group, Alhaji Aliko Dangote, The Chairman BUA group, Alhaji Abdul Samad Rabiu and host of others from the business community will be in attendance. The unveiling will also have in attendance the Royal Fathers led by the Emir of Kano, His Royal highness Alhaji Aminu Ado Bayero.